==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Divagation
<hw>Di`va*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>divagari</ets> to wander about; <ets>di-</ets> = <ets>dis-</ets> +
<ets>vagari</ets> to stroll about: cf. F. <ets>divagation</ets>. See
<er>Vagary</er>.]</ety> <def>A wandering about or going astray;
digression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let us be set down at Queen's Crawley without further
<qex>divagation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Thackeray.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Divalent</ent>⟦br⟧
